Todays Shoulder & Chest workout 😮‍💨
.
1. Seated Shoulder Press Machine 3 x 8-10 Reps
•The goal here is achieve 8-10 reps at failure… if you’re going above 10 add more weight, if you’re getting less than 8 lower the weight! Another point here is not locking out at the top, come just shy of locking the arms and then back down!
.
2. Lateral Shoulder Raise 3 x 12-15
•The goal here is achieve 12-15 reps at failure… if you’re going above 15 add more weight, if you’re getting less than 12 lower the weight! With this movement we want to be bringing the arms up at 45 degree angle… We DON’T want to be coming straight out to the side.
.
3. Front Shoulder Raise 3 x 12-15
•The goal here is achieve 12-15 reps at failure… if you’re going above 15 add more weight, if you’re getting less than 12 lower the weight!
.
4. Incline Dumbbell Bench Press 3 x 8-10
•The goal here is achieve 8-10 reps at failure… if you’re going above 10 add more weight, if you’re getting less than 8 lower the weight! Setup for this exercise you want to lift the bench up only one notch so there’s only a slight incline.
.
5. Seated Chest Press Machine 4 x 10 Each
•The goal here is achieve 20 total reps, 10 reps with added resistance from a partner and 10 regular reps. If you don’t have a partner do 20 total reps with a slow ECCENTRIC potion of the movement! You should be failing at the 20 rep mark
.

Comparing a raw, unedited photo to one that's been retouched serves as a reminder not to take everything at face value on social media. Many individuals heavily edit their pictures to create an idealized image. In my first picture, taken straight from the camera, the natural lighting and post-workout pump play a role. It's not uncommon for people to meet their favorite influencers in person and discover they look vastly different from their online persona.

In the realm of fitness, countless individuals showcase seemingly perfect bodies online. Yet, the truth is, fewer than 5 percent of adults commit to consistent workouts exceeding 30 minutes daily. It's a personal journey, a pursuit of self-improvement with every workout and every choice about what we nourish our bodies with. Ultimately, it's about becoming a better version of ourselves, one step at a time. 🎥💪🏼

Consistency is the key that unlocks your potential. Be in the gym daily, and watch your progress soar 🎥🦍
